    <title>Chole Bhature Recipe</title>
	<link href="~/css/chole.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

 
    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🍛 Chole Bhature</h1>
        

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>

        <h3>For Chole (Chickpea Curry):</h3>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>1 cup Chickpeas (soaked overnight)</li>
            <li>1 large Onion (finely chopped)</li>
            <li>2 Tomatoes (pureed)</li>
            <li>1 tsp Ginger-Garlic Paste</li>
            <li>1 Green Chili (chopped)</li>
            <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp Red Chili Powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp Coriander Powder</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Garam Masala</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Oil</li>
            <li>Fresh Coriander Leaves for garnish</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>For Bhature (Fried Bread):</h3>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>2 cups All-Purpose Flour</li>
            <li>1/4 cup Yogurt</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Baking Soda</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Salt</li>
            <li>Water (as needed)</li>
            <li>Oil for frying</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>

        <h3>Step 1: Cook the Chickpeas</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Pressure cook the soaked chickpeas with water and salt until soft.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Step 2: Prepare the Chole</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Heat oil in a pan, add cumin seeds, and let them splutter.</li>
            <li>Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and green chili, cook for a minute.</li>
            <li>Pour in the tomato puree and cook until oil separates.</li>
            <li>Add turmeric, chili powder, coriander powder, and garam masala.</li>
            <li>Mix in the cooked chickpeas and simmer for 10 minutes.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Step 3: Prepare Bhature</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>In a bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt, and yogurt.</li>
            <li>Add water gradually to make a soft dough.</li>
            <li>Cover and let it rest for 1 hour.</li>
            <li>Roll into circles and deep fry in hot oil until puffed and golden.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Step 4: Serve</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Garnish the chole with fresh coriander.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with crispy bhature!</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
